avatars.description: A typical man who wants a simple, effective solution for visible scalp flakes and itch so he can look confident without a complicated routine.
avatars.key_buying_motivation: Quick, reliable relief from flakes that fits into a simple grooming routine.
avatars.pain_point: Visible dandruff/flakes and occasional itch that undermines confidence in social and professional settings.
avatars.desire: A discreet, proven product that clears flakes fast and requires minimal effort.
failed_alternatives: Home remedies (apple cider vinegar, baking soda)

avatars.description: A mid-career professional who needs a discreet, high-quality treatment to eliminate flakes so his appearance matches his professional standing.
avatars.key_buying_motivation: A clinically-backed product that delivers visible results and feels premium.
avatars.pain_point: Flakes showing on dark suits and collars during meetings, hurting perceived professionalism.
avatars.desire: A trustworthy, premium solution that removes flakes and maintains a polished look.
objections: Is it worth the price vs. cheaper options?
Will it leave residue or scent that conflicts with cologne?
failed_alternatives: Drugstore dandruff shampoos that left hair dry
Over-the-counter medicated shampoos with strong smells
Frequent washing and styling to hide flakes

avatars.description: A young urban man who cares about first impressions and wants a grooming product that both works and looks good on his shelf.
avatars.key_buying_motivation: Effective formula packaged attractively and aligned with personal style.
avatars.pain_point: Flakes that ruin photos or nights out and products that look cheap in his routine.
avatars.desire: A solution that clears flakes, smells pleasant or neutral, and has premium branding.
objections: Product might have a medicinal scent
Not trendy or recommended by influencers
failed_alternatives: Natural/DIY solutions that looked better on Instagram than in practice
Shampoos that strip hair of style
Cosmetic cover-ups like powder which look fake

avatars.description: A sporty man who sweats often and needs a robust, reliable anti-flake treatment that performs despite frequent workouts and helmets.
avatars.key_buying_motivation: A durable formula that prevents flakes even with frequent sweating and washing.
avatars.pain_point: Recurring flakes triggered by sweat, helmets, or frequent washing; concern about product failing under heavy activity.
avatars.desire: A long-lasting, sweat-resistant remedy that keeps scalp clear between washes.
objections: Will it wash out quickly with heavy sweating?
Does it leave hair greasy or heavy?
Is it safe to use frequently?
failed_alternatives: Daily anti-dandruff shampoos that lose effectiveness
Dry shampoos that mask but don’t treat flakes

avatars.description: A man with sensitive or reactive skin who needs a clinically-backed, gentle treatment that won’t cause irritation or dryness.
avatars.key_buying_motivation: A clinically tested, fragrance-free or mild formula proven safe for sensitive scalps.
avatars.pain_point: Irritation, redness, or worsening symptoms from harsh anti-dandruff products.
avatars.desire: A gentle, dermatologist-approved product that reduces flakes without side effects.
failed_alternatives: Medicated shampoos that caused dryness and burning
Prescription products with undesirable side effects

avatars.description: A student or young worker who wants an affordable, effective fix for flakes without committing to expensive regimens.
avatars.key_buying_motivation: Affordable, single-product solution with rapid visible improvement.
avatars.pain_point: Limited budget and impatience with multi-step or expensive treatments that don’t guarantee results.
avatars.desire: A cheap-but-effective product that works quickly and lasts sufficiently long to justify the cost.
objections: Too expensive for a student budget
failed_alternatives: Cheap drugstore brands that didn’t work
Sharing or trying small samples that had no effect
